                <h1>Understanding the Carter Last Name Meaning</h1>
                <p>Carter is a surname of English origin, derived from the Old French term "carriero," meaning "one who transports goods by cart." Historically, it refers to a profession involving cart drivers or transporters. Over time, the name has evolved into a common surname, often associated with strength and dependability.</p>
